cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV 

This paper is about generating natural adversarial text to attack machine learning models in natural language tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the effectiveness and efficiency of the proposed method, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper deals with adversarial attacks, it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper uses pre-trained models, which could suggest a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
